South Africa Has Little Rate ‘Flexibility,’ Business Day Says, Citing S&P

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-04-29T05:14:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/south-africa-has-little-rate-flexibility-business-day-says-citing-s-p.html
Standard & Poor’s  said  South Africa 
has little “monetary policy flexibility” because of the
country’s reliance on portfolio inflows and its low savings
rate, Business Day reported, citing a report by the credit
ratings company.  The report said the government’s “fiscal flexibility” is
also constrained because of rising debt levels, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper added.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nasreen Seria at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net  